race.comment: ICONIC PRINCE (2) got a well-deserved Mackay victory at the latest effort and will have derived a stack of confidence from that overdue win. Winning rider Cormack sticks in the irons and can go back-to-back without shocking. GRUMPYWANTSATISSUE (8) is a consistent conveyance who has hit the top-five at his past seven starts and is usually thereabouts. Best form puts him right in this. ROY'S ROAD (9) is drawn to get a gun run in transit from the inside marble and rates a must for the exotics players. CITIROC (4) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated. The very well-related I SAY BOOM (1) (half to 6xG1 winner Chautauqua) best of the rest.
